NAF.raw: http : / / www . mirror . co . uk / news / uk - news / john - jenkin - goth - son - held - 1942506 John Jenkin : Goth son held as mum and sister killed 10 Jun 2013 09 : 10 John Jenkin , 23 , was arrested near the terraced house where Alice McMeekin , 58 , and Katie Jenkin , 20 , and a dead dog , thought to be the family's pet collie , were discovered A goth was being questioned on suspicion of murder yesterday after his mother and sister were found dead at home . John Jenkin , 23 , was arrested near the terraced house where Alice McMeekin , 58 , and Katie Jenkin , 20 , and a dead dog , thought to be the family's pet collie , were discovered . Police were called by neighbours at breakfast time on Saturday after they heard piercing screams coming from the house . One said : "I heard screaming , really high - pitched screams in the early hours . Then later I heard more screaming . It sounded like someone telling a dog to shut up . " Alice lived in the pebble - dashed terrace in Millom , Cumbria , with �unemployed John . The neighbour described him as a goth and he is said to have recently been in hospital . Katie was visiting her mum from Cardiff , where she was at university . A close friend of the dead mum said : "I can't believe it . They all looked after each other after Alice separated from her husband in the 1990s . We were so close that Katie thought of my mum as a second mum . "John was a good kid , never one of those to get into trouble . He idolised his mum and his sister . His little sister was his world , and his mum was too . " Alice was brought up in Millom , where her father ran a greengrocer's and a fish shop . She returned to her home town 12 weeks ago after a four year spell living in Cardiff . Friends noticed she had lost weight and looked frail . It is thought she may have been suffering from cancer . Another neighbour added : "She went down to Wales to give her kids a better life . Katie got into Cardiff University , I think , and John was at college doing something in special effects . "When Alice came home , John came with her . As far as I know he didn't have a girlfriend . Katie still lived in Wales and had been going out with her boyfriend for two years . "She came up for the weekend on Friday . Alice met her at the station . " Security worker Alice had recently been upset by the death of one of her four cats and had taken in a collie dog called Fenn . The friend said she was "bubbly" when she saw her on Friday . She added : "We were chatting for about half an hour . She told me Katie was coming and she was so looking forward to it . " Cumbria Police have not disclosed how Alice and Katie died . A police spokesman said : "We do not suspect anyone else to be involved . " Detective Chief Inspector Paul Duhig said : "Events such as these are rare in Cumbria . We are doing all we can to bring the offender to justice . "
